\b INTRODUCTION
\b0 \
\
iOS developers have three choices for allowing users to enter numerical data:\
(1) 
\f1 UITextField
\f0  + 
\f1 UIKeyboard
\f0 \
(2) 
\f1 UISlider
\f0  control\
(3) 
\f1 UIPickerView
\f0 \
\
Each has some weakness, depending on the need.  Keyboarding on the iPhone is not ergonomic and the 
\f1 UISlider
\f0  control doesn't present scaling landmarks or "snap-to-grid" functionality.  Finally, the 
\f1 UIPickerView
\f0  occupies a large area of the screen and may not be desirable if other controls or data need to be placed.\
\
Enter CCFNumberPicker.\
\

