\b USAGE
\b0 \
\
The header files should have sufficient documentation (formatted for Doxygen) to get you started.  You mainly need to be concerned about two classes:  
\f1 CCFNumberPickerView
\f0  and 
\f1 CCFNumberPickerData
\f0 .  You may instantiate the former either programmatically or in a nib.  This is the superview of a hierarchy that draws the picker view.  
\f1 CCFNumberPickerData
\f0  is a model object that encapsulates data about the formatting of the picker view.  Lastly, take a look at the sample project's view controller. That shows you most of what you need to know to use the classes.\
